<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="18" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,499,1106]" box="[198,583,538,564]" pageId="11" pageNumber="18">
2 genera (
<emphasis box="[315,566,538,563]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="18">
<taxonomicName box="[315,421,538,563]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Davalliaceae" genus="Davallia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="11" pageNumber="18" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Davallia</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[433,566,538,563]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Davalliaceae" genus="Davallodes" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="11" pageNumber="18" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Davallodes</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,499,1106]" box="[198,1201,577,603]" pageId="11" pageNumber="18">
Reference: 
<bibRefCitation author="Kato, M. &amp; Tsutsumi, C." box="[332,621,577,603]" pageId="11" pageNumber="18" pagination="1 - 14" refId="ref15068" refString="Kato, M. &amp; Tsutsumi, C. (2009) Generic classification of Davalliaceae. Acta Phytotaxonomica Geobotanica 59: 1 - 14." type="journal article" year="2009">Kato &amp; Tsutsumi (2009)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Tsutsumi, C. &amp; Kato, M." box="[634,923,577,603]" pageId="11" pageNumber="18" pagination="495 - 510" refId="ref21469" refString="Tsutsumi, C. &amp; Kato, M. (2006) Evolution of epiphytes in Davalliaceae and related ferns. Botanical Journal of the Linnean Society 151: 495 - 510." type="journal article" year="2006">Tsutsumi &amp; Kato (2006)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Tsutsumi, C. &amp; Zhang, X. - C. &amp; Kato, M." box="[935,1198,577,603]" pageId="11" pageNumber="18" pagination="44 - 48" refId="ref21502" refString="Tsutsumi, C., Zhang, X. - C. &amp; Kato, M. (2008) Molecular phylogeny of Davalliaceae and implications for generic classification. Systematic Botany 33: 44 - 48." type="journal article" year="2008">
Tsutsumi 
<emphasis box="[1050,1108,577,602]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="18">et al.</emphasis>
(2008)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,499,1106]" pageId="11" pageNumber="18">
Note:â€”Tsutsumi and collaborators (2006, 2008) provided a phylogeny of the 
<taxonomicName box="[1111,1265,616,642]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Davalliaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="11" pageNumber="18" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Davalliaceae</taxonomicName>
, in which they found 
<taxonomicName box="[235,346,655,680]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Davalliaceae" genus="Davallia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="11" pageNumber="18" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[235,346,655,680]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="18">Davallia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to be polyphyletic and proposed to recognise the 5 clades at the generic level. This classification creates an inflated number of genera and an alternative two genera concept can also be considered. They proposed the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Kato &amp; Tsutsumi (2008)" authorityName="Kato &amp; Tsutsumi" authorityYear="2008" box="[637,1140,732,758]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Davalliaceae" genus="Araiostegiella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="11" pageNumber="18" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[637,817,732,757]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="18">Araiostegiella</emphasis>
Kato &amp; 
<bibRefCitation author="Tsutsumi, C. &amp; Zhang, X. - C. &amp; Kato, M." box="[931,1140,732,758]" pageId="11" pageNumber="18" pagination="44 - 48" refId="ref21502" refString="Tsutsumi, C., Zhang, X. - C. &amp; Kato, M. (2008) Molecular phylogeny of Davalliaceae and implications for generic classification. Systematic Botany 33: 44 - 48." type="journal article" year="2008">Tsutsumi (2008)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and reinstated 
<taxonomicName authority="Bernhardi (1801: 122)" authorityName="Bernhardi" authorityPageNumber="122" authorityYear="1801" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Davalliaceae" genus="Wibelia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="11" pageNumber="18" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1340,1436,732,757]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="18">Wibelia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Bernhardi, D. I. I." box="[151,415,770,796]" pageId="11" pageNumber="18" pagination="121 - 136" refId="ref11365" refString="Bernhardi, D. I. I. (1801) Tentamen alterum filices in genera redigendi. Journal fur die Botanik (Schrader) 1800 (2): 121 - 136." type="journal article" year="1801">Bernhardi (1801: 122)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, the latter being a later homonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="Gaertner et al. (1801: 97" authorityName="Gaertner" authorityYear="1801" box="[847,1235,770,796]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Wibelia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="11" pageNumber="18" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[847,936,770,795]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="18">Wibelia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Gaertner, P. G. &amp; Meyer, B. &amp; Scherbius, J." box="[944,1235,770,796]" pageId="11" pageNumber="18" refId="ref13352" refString="Gaertner, P. G., Meyer, B. &amp; Scherbius, J. (1801), Oekonomisch-Technische Flora der Wetterau 3, abt. 1. Philipp Heinrich Guilhauman. Frankfurt am Main." type="book" year="1801">
Gaertner 
<emphasis box="[1054,1112,770,795]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="18">et al.</emphasis>
(1801: 97
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 144), a genus of 
<taxonomicName box="[151,279,809,835]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="11" pageNumber="18" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Asteraceae</taxonomicName>
(= 
<taxonomicName box="[320,397,809,834]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Cymuloporidae" genus="Crepis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="11" pageNumber="18" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[320,397,809,834]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="18">Crepis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and thus a new genus is needed to accommodate for 
<taxonomicName authority="P.G.Gaertner, B.Meyer &amp; Scherbius, 1801" authorityName="P.G.Gaertner, B.Meyer &amp; Scherbius" authorityYear="1801" box="[1038,1373,809,835]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Wibelia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="11" pageNumber="18" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[1038,1127,809,834]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="18">Wibelia</emphasis>
Bernh. Most species
</taxonomicName>
have combinations in 
<taxonomicName box="[351,455,848,873]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Davalliaceae" genus="Davallia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="11" pageNumber="18" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[351,455,848,873]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="18">Davallia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and it seems appropriate to consider a broader concept for 
<taxonomicName box="[1171,1275,848,873]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Davalliaceae" genus="Davallia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="11" pageNumber="18" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1171,1275,848,873]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="18">Davallia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
that includes 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kato &amp; Tsutsumi" authorityYear="2008" box="[151,326,887,912]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Davalliaceae" genus="Araiostegiella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="11" pageNumber="18" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,326,887,912]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="18">Araiostegiella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" box="[389,487,887,912]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Davalliaceae" genus="Humata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="11" pageNumber="18" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[389,487,887,912]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="18">Humata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. To divide 
<taxonomicName box="[632,740,887,912]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Davalliaceae" genus="Davallia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="11" pageNumber="18" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[632,740,887,912]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="18">Davallia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the issue remains to which of the five clades the name 
<taxonomicName box="[151,254,925,950]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Davalliaceae" genus="Davallia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="11" pageNumber="18" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,254,925,950]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="18">Davallia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be applied, because the geographically isolated 
<taxonomicName box="[916,1089,925,950]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Davalliaceae" genus="Davallia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="11" pageNumber="18" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="canariensis">
<emphasis box="[916,1089,925,950]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="18">D. canariensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(L.) Sm., the 
<typeStatus box="[1257,1308,925,951]" pageId="11" pageNumber="18">type</typeStatus>
species, is not included in these studies. Without establishing to which clade this species belongs, a generic subdivision will be difficult to validate. 
<taxonomicName box="[490,626,1002,1027]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Davalliaceae" genus="Davallodes" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="11" pageNumber="18" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[490,626,1002,1027]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="18">Davallodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(incl. 
<taxonomicName authority="Copeland, 1927" authorityName="Copeland" authorityYear="1927" box="[706,846,1002,1027]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Davalliaceae" genus="Araiostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="11" pageNumber="18" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[706,846,1002,1027]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="18">Araiostegia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) as treated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Tsutsumi, C. &amp; Zhang, X. - C. &amp; Kato, M." box="[1026,1292,1002,1028]" pageId="11" pageNumber="18" pagination="44 - 48" refId="ref21502" refString="Tsutsumi, C., Zhang, X. - C. &amp; Kato, M. (2008) Molecular phylogeny of Davalliaceae and implications for generic classification. Systematic Botany 33: 44 - 48." type="journal article" year="2008">
Tsutsumi 
<emphasis box="[1144,1204,1002,1027]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="18">et al.</emphasis>
(2008)
</bibRefCitation>
is followed here, reducing the number of genera to two, but this may require updating using an improved phylogegentic analyses in the near future.
</paragraph>
